The cabinet has approved a bill making iteasier for the government to issue commemorative coins, aFinance Ministry official said.    The bill, which must still be approved by parliament, wouldtake effect in April 1988. It would allow the government toissue 1,000, 5,000 and 10,000 yen coins without speciallegislation, although higher-valued coins would still need aspecial law, the official said. At present it can only issuecoins of 500 yen or less. REUTER&#3;